Maurice Crittenden, a British journalist, in The Sunday Times, Oct. 24, 1998, stated that one of Lady Thatcher's political allies, Labour politician Woodrow Wyatt, believed Beatrice Stephenson was the illegitimate daughter of society figure Harry Cust and his married servant Phoebe Stephenson (n&lt;U+00E9&gt;e Crust, Mrs Daniel Stephenson). One of Cust's known illegitimate children was Lady Diana Cooper, who knew of the rumor and reportedly found it amusing to refer to Prime Minister Thatcher as her niece (John Campbell, Margaret Thatcher, Jonathan Cape, 2000, Volume I, page 5). The Cust-Roberts story was restated by Crittenden in an article published in 2006 and accessible at the website of the Margaret Thatcher Foundation, http://www.margaretthatcher.org/commentary/displaydocument.asp?docid=110880



