Observer Profile of Carol Thatcher 27 November 2005








In July 2002, theatre producer Paul Kelleher, 37, decapitated a &lt;U+00A3&gt;150,000,  marble sculpture of Thatcher. Using a cricket bat hidden in his trousers, Kelleher took a swipe at the statue on display at the Guildhall Art Gallery, central London. When he failed to knock off the head, he grabbed a metal pole to complete the act.  See also  He was jailed.















